Breakfast is in a large hall, illuminated by very cool blue lighting, although it does make it quite dark - but if you don't want to read the paper at breakfast, it's fine.	There is a nice relaxing and calm ambience in the large bar/reception area which is great for unwinding with a drink at the end of a busy days sightseeing!	It was very basic, and looked like it hadn't been renovated (other than to update the furniture) since the mid-nineties.	I was extremely pleasantly surprised by the luxurious and comfortable centrally located hotel, which far surpassed my expectations of a chain hotel in its size and atmosphere.